properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 3:04PM CST until February 12 at 6:00PM CST by NWS North Platte NE
properties.description:
...POTENTIALLY DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS TONIGHT AND THURSDAY MORNING...

.North winds will combine with bitterly cold air, producing wind
chills as low as 29 below zero across north central Nebraska.

* WHAT...For the Winter Weather Advisory, snow. Additional snow
accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 45
mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
expected. Wind chills as low as 29 below zero.

* WHERE...Holt and Boyd Counties.

* WHEN...For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 6 PM CST this
evening. For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 6 PM this evening
to 10 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as
little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

Call Nebraska 511 for the latest road information.
